Radial nerve

  • The radial nerve is the largest branch of the brachial plexus
  • Most frequently injured branch of both the posterior cord as well as the brachial plexus

Root value

C5, 6, 7, 8 and T1

Formation

Originates as a terminal branch of the posterior cord of the brachial plexus

Posterior division of brachial plexus supplies extensors.

Posterior divisions of all trunks unite to form posterior cord.
